<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="172" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,1267,1401]" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">
So far only one record for 
<collectingCountry box="[448,530,1267,1293]" name="Austria" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">Austria</collectingCountry>
was published (
<bibRefCitation author="Reemer, M. &amp; Hauser, M. &amp; Speight, M. C. D." box="[712,933,1267,1294]" pageId="21" pageNumber="172" pagination="553 - 580" refId="ref21209" refString="Reemer, M., Hauser, M. &amp; Speight, M. C. D. (2005) The genus Myolepta Newman in the West-Palaearctic region (Diptera, Syrphidae). Studia dipterologica, 11, 553 - 580." type="journal article" year="2005">
Reemer 
<emphasis box="[808,858,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">et al</emphasis>
. 2005
</bibRefCitation>
). The specimen is deposited in the collection of the Natural History Museum Leiden (
<collectingCountry box="[602,744,1303,1330]" name="Netherlands" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">Netherlands</collectingCountry>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Coe" authorityYear="1957" box="[762,991,1303,1329]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="172" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigritarsis">
<emphasis box="[762,991,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">Myolepta nigritarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs preferentially in old oak forests. It can occur syntopic with other species of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[741,847,1339,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="172" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[741,847,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">Myolepta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, e.g., 
<taxonomicName authority="(Becher, 1882)" baseAuthorityName="Becher" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[914,1214,1339,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="172" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis box="[914,1041,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">M. obscura</emphasis>
(Becher, 1882)
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authority="(Panzer, 1788)" baseAuthorityName="Panzer" baseAuthorityYear="1788" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="172" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vara">
<emphasis box="[1250,1338,1340,1365]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">M. vara</emphasis>
(Panzer, 1788)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
